a very handsome person that is.

"welcome. you must be taehyung."

the said male nods. he'd already made his appointment a day before.

"right this way." the male gestures a heavily tatted arm towards the same door.

taehyung walks by the male, getting a whif of his musky scent.

he feels the tip of his ears burn. and he gulps.

getting a tattoo 'cuz of a dare was bad enough. getting one by the hands of a hot artist changes the whole story.

he just hopes he won't do anything too embarassing.

"hello?" he calls.

a soft voice answers him a few seconds later. "just a moment!"

the voice comes from behind a half open door. taehyung doesn't dare peak.

he stands awkwardly in the middle of the lobby-like place. shifting from one leg to the other.

"you've already filled us in with the details of your tattoo so we can get right into it." says the artist.

he smiles at taehyung, laughing a little when the latter avoids his eyes.

cute.

taehyung sits on the chair as instructed. he takes a deep breathe-

he enters the room to find the client chair in the middle of the space. surrounded by a bunch of stuff he doesn't know the name of.

"sit down and make yourself comfortable."

taehyung nearly jumps when the voice commands from behind him.
